replies.bodyText:
I would suspect so. It would kinda seem Fast AI is not really a true AI but a variant of ProAI. Given that, I would personally look to see if we can inject behavior to a ProAI class.
EG:
FastAI extends ProAi{
   FastAI() {
      super(ProAiConfig.builder()
             .battleCalcImplementation(new FastAiBattleCalc())
             .build());
   }
}

LaboriousAi extends ProAi{
   LaboriousAiI() {
      super(ProAiConfig.builder()
             .battleCalcImplementation(new LaboriousBattleCalc())
             .build());
   }
}

Or even better, do the above as constructor args.

